{
  "stem": "14168.4",
  "chunk_idx": 11,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.3,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "Another miracle happened to me when I was shipped back from Holland to Germany.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "I was able to talk myself out of-- out of the-- going to concentration camp.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And then, I must say, a very-- one of the most moving events when we were on-board the vessel, the first Friday evening services on the vessel.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "It felt almost like we had left Mitzrayim.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "We had a young rabbi who went to Chile with his family.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "He held services for us on Shabbat morning.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And he was talking about going to an uncertain future, like the Israelites of thousands of years ago, and that we have escaped the hell of Germany-- that we will make our way in the new country, whatever may be awaiting us.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "It was-- we almost felt that we had been saved by a miracle.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Yes.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "When I saw that happen, I had the feeling that was one of the greatest tragedy [BACKROUND NOISE] since the destruction of the temple.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I must say, speaking of that, when I mentioned that I felt blessed, I want to add one thing.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My generation has seen two things happen-- the worst misfortune that befell the Jewish people since the destruction of the temple, but then less than 10 years later, the realization of the 2,000-year-old dream, the reestablishment of the Jewish state in Israel.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "How providence, fate, or God works, we don't know.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "We can't understand him, or it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I feel we cannot judge God.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "There's so many things we don't know.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "But to have been blessed with, A, saving my own family, leading a productive life here, and witnessing a 2,000-year-old dream come true, is something that very few people, except the members of my generation, have seen or will see.",
      "word_count": 40
    }
  ],
